stm32mp2-gpu-userspace for OpenSTLinux-compatible ARM64 rootfs
===============================================================

This package contains the ARM64 STM32MP2-specific ST Vivante GCNANO runtime
closure extracted from:

  @INSTALLER@

It implements the same default userspace surface selected by ST's
OpenSTLinux `gcnano-userland-binary` recipe:

  EGL, GBM, GLESv1, GLESv2 and OpenVG

The vendor libraries are placed under:

  @LIBDIR@

and activated first through `/etc/ld.so.conf.d/00-stm32mp2-gpu.conf`. The
package declares `Provides`, `Conflicts` and `Replaces` for only the matching
generic/Mesa API packages, so APT will remove the old EGL/GBM/GLES provider
rather than leaving two providers selected unpredictably.

The following components are intentionally retained from the base rootfs and
are not replaced: `libdrm`, Wayland, desktop OpenGL/GLX, GLVND, Mesa DRI
software drivers, OpenCL and Vulkan. The binary recipe does not enable the
latter two by default. The package refuses installation on a GLVND rootfs
(`libglvnd0` installed), because the ST GCNANO EGL implementation is a direct
non-GLVND provider.

Verify dynamic-linker selection after installation:

  /usr/lib/stm32mp2-gpu/graphics-stack-check
  ldconfig -p | grep -E 'libEGL|libgbm|libGLES|libOpenVG'

The package requires the matching `galcore` kernel module and STM32MP2 GPU
platform configuration. It cannot add a missing GPU device-tree node, clocks,
power domains, CMA reservation or DRM/KMS support.

Upstream commit: @UPSTREAM_COMMIT@
